r the user.\r\n\r\nHere\'s the thing, next to no one visits your site to check out the design; they are looking for information or are trying to complete some action. If they are not noticing the design, it means it is not getting in their way and conforms to the content. As long as everything is intuitive and the content is easy to find and consume, the look and feel is secondary at best. You could layout the content to make it look like a text file with a menu and search, and no one would care if they can easily get what they came for. Boring yes, but it remains functional and fulfills its purpose. Have you ever paid any attention to the design of Google\'s main page and search results? Or have you seldom noticed it? I\'ll agree that the UI in some Google products is not the best, but their main line - search - is excellent even though it looks boring. And you know why? because it functions exceptionally well, my grandma can use it like a pro, and it gives you what you want. It\'s the very reason Google rose to mind blowing success nearly overnight.\r\n\r\nI\'m not trying to piss anybody off, design is hard and important, but it becomes counter-productive if your number one concern is not the user. Humans appreciate visual appeal, to a certain threshold based on context. Unless I\'m looking to hire a creative, I\'m mostly indifferent to your site\'s design, unless it\'s annoying . I\'m not on your website to appreciate art. Don\'t overload my senses please.','Creative','','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-12-24 06:49:48','2017-12-24 06:49:48','',6,'http://derulski.local/?p=20',0,'revision','',0),(21,1,'2017-12-24 06:50:11','2017-12-24 06:50:11','Grab a dictionary. look up \'creative.\'\r\n\r\n\"relating to or involving the imagination or original ideas, especially in the production of an artistic work.\"\r\n\r\nIf we go by this definition, then nearly all the people involved in the creation of webpages, aside from copywriters, are not crea